DATA CLOUD
Set Up an Elasticsearch Connection (Beta)

Create a connection to import data from Elasticsearch into Data Cloud.

REQUIRED USER PERMISSIONS

	User Permissions Needed
To create a connection:	

Data Cloud Admin

OR

Data Cloud Marketing Admin

NOTE This feature is a Beta Service. Customers may opt to try a Beta Service using their own discretion. Any use of the Beta Service is subject to the applicable Beta Services Terms provided at Agreements and Terms.

Before you begin:

Make sure that the Elasticsearch connector is enabled. See Enable Data Cloud Features..
Review IP Addresses Used by Data Cloud Services to make sure that the Elasticsearch connector has the necessary access.
In Data Cloud, click Setup, and select Data Cloud Setup.
Under Configuration, select Connectors.
On the Source tab, select Elasticsearch and click Next.
Enter a connection name, connection API name, and provide the authentication and connection details.
In Authentication Details, enter your username and password.
In Connection Details, enter the host name in Connection URL, and Port.
To review your configuration, click Test Configuration.
Click Save.

After the connector details are accepted, the connection is created and ready to use. It’s listed under Connectors.

A Data Aware Specialist can now create data streams.
